Links: [{"title":"Add iOS 18 Zoom Navigation Transitions To A SwiftUI Grid | The Swift Dev","url":"https://www.theswift.dev/posts/swiftui-zoom-navigation-transition/"},{"title":"Zoom transitions - Douglas Hill","url":"https://douglashill.co/zoom-transitions/"},{"title":"Using the zoom navigation transition in SwiftUI","url":"https://www.createwithswift.com/using-the-zoom-navigation-transition-in-swiftui/"},{"title":"iOS 18 Zoom navigation transition · Issue #25 · hmlongco/Navigator","url":"https://github.com/hmlongco/Navigator/issues/25"},{"title":"How to create zoom animations between views - a free SwiftUI by Example tutorial","url":"https://www.hackingwithswift.com/quick-start/swiftui/how-to-create-zoom-animations-between-views"},{"title":"[SwiftUI]NavigationTransition. NavigationTransition | by ganeshrajugalla | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@ganeshrajugalla/swiftui-navigationtransition-e44b1032cf0e"},{"title":"SwiftUI | Apple Developer Forums","url":"https://developer.apple.com/forums/topics/ui-frameworks-topic/ui-frameworks-topic-swiftui?page=4&sortBy=newest"},{"title":"matchedTransitionSource(id:in:) | Apple Developer Documentation","url":"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/view/matchedtransitionsource(id:in:)"}]

Based on my search, here's what I found about the SwiftUI zoom navigation transition availability on macOS:

## The Core Issue

The zoom navigation transition is **not available on macOS**, even though the broader navigation transition API technically exists there. The broader NavigationTransition protocol is available on macOS 15, but the ZoomNavigationTransition type is marked unavailable on macOS in the current SDK, so you should keep this code in an iOS or iPadOS availability boundary.

## Platform Availability

The ZoomNavigationTransition API is available starting in iOS 18, iPadOS 18, tvOS 18, watchOS 11, and visionOS 2. Notably, macOS is absent from this list for the `.zoom` transition specifically.

The two related modifiers work together: use the `matchedTransitionSource()` modifier on whatever source view is triggering the transition, and use the `navigationTransition()` modifier on whatever destination view you're navigating to. Both modifiers must be given a stable view ID that is being transitioned, just like matched geometry effects.

## How to Handle the macOS Limitation

The recommended approach is to wrap the zoom transition code in platform and availability checks so it gracefully degrades. Here's the pattern from one of the sources:

```swift
extension View {
    @ViewBuilder
    func zoomTransitionSource<ID: Hashable>(
        id: ID, in namespace: Namespace.ID
